    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-07-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-09-01T20:39:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Predatory Lending Sunset Act - Amends the Truth in Lending Act to limit the maximum interest rate which a creditor may charge on a covered consumer credit loan of up to $3,000 to an annual percentage rate (APR) of 36%.</p> <p>Prohibits a creditor from extending a covered loan with respect to which the creditor uses as security either: (1) access to a borrower's financial account; or (2) the title of a vehicle.</p> <p>Amends the Electronic Fund Transfer Act to prohibit a remotely created check that: (1) is not created by the financial institution that holds the customer account from which the check is to be paid; and (2) does not bear a signature applied by the person from whose account the check is to be paid.</p>  <p>Declares unenforceable, with respect to any consumer, any contract made in violation of this Act.</p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
